CLKComplicationSupportedFamilies.description: Specifies the complication families for which the app can provide data. See CLKComplicationSupportedFamilies for details.

CLKComplicationPrincipalClass.description: Specifies the name of the class that implements the complication data source protocol. See CLKComplicationPrincipalClass for details.

WKAppBundleIdentifier.description: Specifies the bundle ID of the Watch app. See WKAppBundleIdentifier for details.

WKBackgroundModes.description: Provides execution time, for a WatchKit extension running in the background, to update UI values in its app or to perform view navigation for workout processing. See WKBackgroundModes for details.

WKCompanionAppBundleIdentifier.description: Specifies the bundle ID of the companion iOS app. See WKCompanionAppBundleIdentifier for details.

WKExtensionDelegateClassName.description: Specifies the name of the class that manages lifecycle events for the WatchKit extension. See WKExtensionDelegateClassName for details.

WKWatchKitApp.description: Specifies a Boolean indicating whether the app is the launchable Watch app. See WKWatchKitApp for details.
